        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-5">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-xs-12">
                        <div class="brand">SEO Text Editor</div>
                        <h1 class="slogan hidden-xs"><span class="hidden-xs hidden-sm">&bull; </span>Cross-checks keywords<span class="hidden-md hidden-lg"> &bull; </span><p class="hidden-xs hidden-sm"></p><span class="hidden-xs hidden-sm">&bull; </span>Shows text length in pixels, chars, words<span class="hidden-md hidden-lg"> &bull; </span><p class="hidden-xs hidden-sm"></p><span class="hidden-xs hidden-sm">&bull; </span>SERP preview</h1>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row hidden-xs hidden-sm">
                    <div class="col-xs-12">
                        <div class="intro">
                            <div class="well">
                                <p><strong>This SEO Text Editor enables editors to write consistent, SEO optimised texts.</strong></p>
                                <p>The tool checks the field length of Title, Meta Description, Heading 1 and the Copy itself. Additionally, Keywords are cross-checked to make sure they appear consistently in the various fields. At the same time it ignores
                                    German and English Stop Words. Last but not least, a SERP preview is available.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="panel panel-default">
                                <div class="panel-heading">
                                    <h2 class="panel-title">Applied SEO rules</h2>
                                </div>
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Common English and German stopwords are ignored.</li>
                                        <li>Character and pixel count are validated and displayed above the input fields.</li>
                                        <li>Keywords in the <strong>Title</strong> need to appear in the Text.</li>
                                        <li>Keywords in the <strong>Title</strong> are not to be repeated in the Title.</li>
                                        <li>Keywords in the <strong>Headline 1</strong> need to appear in the Text.</li>
                                        <li>At least 3 Keywords in the <strong>Meta Description</strong> need to appear in the Text.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
            <div class="col-md-7">
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="serp-box" class="name">SERP Preview</label>
                    <div id="serp-box" class="panel">
                        <div>
                            <a href="#" id="serp-title">Write Title Tags that Describe the Content</a>
                        </div>
                        <div id="serp-url-desc">
                            <div id="serp-url">www.example.com/</div>
                            <div id="serp-desc">Use meta descriptions to describe your page content. Google uses relevant meta descriptions to create the snippet that Describe your page in SERP listings.</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <form>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="url" class="name">URL</label><span id="url-warning" class="label label-warning"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-warning" aria-hidden="true"></span> Entering an URL will update all fields!</span>
                        <label id="url-spinner"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-repeat normal-right-spinner"></span> Please wait...</label>

                        <!-- label class="error" id="url-length"></label -->
                        <div class="form-control" id="url" placeholder="www.example.com/"></div>
                        <!-- div id="url-quality"></div -->
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="title" class="name">Site Title</label><label class="error lengthLow" id="title-length"></label>
                        <div class="editable form-control" id="title" placeholder="Write Title Tags that Describe the Content and Encourages Clicks"></div>
                        <div id="title-quality">
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-xs-12">&nbsp;</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="description" class="name">Meta Description</label><label class="error lengthLow" id="description-length"></label>
                        <div id="description" class="form-control editable textarea" placeholder="Use meta descriptions to describe your page content. Google uses relevant meta descriptions to create the snippet that Describe your page in SERP listings."></div>
                        <div id="description-quality"></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="h1" class="name">Heading 1</label><label class="error lengthLow" id="h1-length"></label>
                        <div class="form-control editable" id="h1" placeholder="Use keywords in the headline."></div>
                        <div id="h1-quality"></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="text" class="name">Text</label><label class="error lengthLow" id="text-length"></label>
                        <div id="text" class="form-control editable textarea scrollable" placeholder="Write a text that contains keywords from the title, description and headline."></div>
                        <div id="text-quality">
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-xs-12">&nbsp;</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
